    "title": "LESSON 18: REFLEXIVE PRONOUNS",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "Some verbs refer back to the subject,",
          "like in English: I take care of myself.",
          "",
          "REFLEXIVE PRONOUNS:",
          "ich → mich     wir → uns",
          "du → dich      ihr → euch",
          "er/sie/es → sich    sie/Sie → sich",
          "",
          "TRUE REFLEXIVE VERBS (always reflexive):",
          "sich freuen (be happy), sich erinnern (remember)",
          "Ich freue mich! (I'm happy)",
          "",
          "OPTIONAL REFLEXIVE (changes meaning):",
          "anziehen = to put on (something)",
          "sich anziehen = to get dressed",
          "",
          "Ich ziehe die Jacke an. (I put on the jacket)",
          "Ich ziehe mich an. (I get dressed)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion achtzehn"
      }
    ]
  },
